    <updated>2024-09-03T15:34:20.869000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>gregorw</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/12545</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;If you want to use the onPrem MySQL DB as your CAP persistence you need to check if &lt;A href="https://github.com/Soontao/cds-mysql" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://github.com/Soontao/cds-mysql&lt;/A&gt; would support connecting to the DB via Cloud Connector. To support this a TCP Endpoint (the MySQL Server) must be exposed in SAP Cloud Connector and the cds-mysql adapter would need to support connections via the SOCKS5 proxy.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;If that is not an option you could try to run a CAP application using the&amp;nbsp;cds-mysql adapter onPrem and consume its exposed APIs via the Destination.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/re-connecting-to-mysql-from-capm-application/qaq-p/13853062/comment-id/4881712#M4881712"/>
    <published>2024-09-03T15:34:20.869000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
